## Limitations
This report is limited by the availability of recent data and the inherent biases present in opinion pieces and organizational reports. Additionally, the complexity of the criminal justice system means that perspectives can vary widely based on individual experiences and regional differences. Further research, including empirical studies and longitudinal data, would provide a more comprehensive understanding of the system's fairness.